name: a glimpse into the past
description:
Photo taken in June 2021,  1/3200 sec. F2.8 50mm, 4000 5340 px 
It was 12 in the morning and the light was burning, but that look was even stronger, it called something but I did not know from where. Until I came to reshape the image making it nocturnal and reflecting it. 

The ghosts of the past struggle to leave because of a present that distracts little. Because of a look that is often too lucid to live on this earth. 
But the past is within us and not outside, and even in there it is not preserved intact, but the past also changes.
